  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>bulgur</strong> <strong>wheat</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook over a high heat for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once tender, drain and set aside in a sieve to cool</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1633444749626-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1633444749626-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1633444749626-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1633444749626-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1633444749626-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> meat-free mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627035061119-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627035061119-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627035061119-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627035061119-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1627035061119-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Carefully discard any excess oil from the pan, then stir in your <strong>ras el hanout</strong> and cook for 1 min</p><p>Sprinkle in your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and add a splash of <strong>cold water</strong>, then give everything a good mix up</p><p>Reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for a further 3-4 min or until the meat-free mince is cooked through</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1633444765203-x200.jpg",
